        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 5:34PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 533 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Us-87 Near The Mason-
Gillespie County Line, or near Cherry Spring, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Loyal Valley, Hilda, and Us-87 Near The Mason-Gillespie County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
